# Stock Search Dashboard Walkthrough

The development of the Bento Grid-based stock market dashboard is complete. It employs a modern tech stack centered on **React**, **Tailwind CSS**, and **Framer Motion**, delivering an immediate sense of premium aesthetic.

## Architecture and Components

- **[App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/14L1/Desktop/Bento-grid/src/App.tsx)**: The main layout structure containing a sidebar navigation and the primary grid area.
- **[BentoGrid.tsx](file:///c:/Users/14L1/Desktop/Bento-grid/src/components/BentoGrid.tsx)**: Reusable grid components utilizing Tailwind CSS Grid layout utilities and Framer Motion effects. Highlights hovered items with dynamic border changes.
- **StockChart.tsx / Watchlist.tsx / SearchWidget.tsx**: Handcrafted components that fulfill the specific goal of a typical quantitative trading platform. Recharts was integrated natively to create a beautiful data visualization area.

## Key Technical Details

- **Tailwind configuration in [tailwind.config.js](file:///c:/Users/14L1/Desktop/Bento-grid/tailwind.config.js)** injects unified color tokens (`background`, `card`, `success`, `danger`), setting up a dark mode system specifically.
- Framer Motion provides lightweight interaction behaviors on the grid elements.
- Uses `class-variance-authority` pattern manually to concatenate classes gracefully with `tailwind-merge`.

## Result

Your dashboard is currently running on the Vite development server (usually available at `http://localhost:5173`). Have a look to test all layout spans!

> [!TIP]
> The UI includes various micro-interactions. Try clicking inputs, hovering over the stock cards on the Watchlist, and interacting with the primary chart context to evaluate the UX flow.
